<item>
            <title>[SPR-8056] Decide what to do with &apos;local&apos; attribute in beans: namespace</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-8056</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As mentioned in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-8054&quot; title=&quot;Since the introduction of nested &amp;quot;beans&amp;quot; element, &amp;quot;id&amp;quot; is no longer of type xsd:ID&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-8054&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-8054&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, the use of the &lt;tt&gt;local&lt;/tt&gt; attribute in &lt;tt&gt;beans:&lt;/tt&gt; namespace is no longer of much value now that bean &lt;tt&gt;id&lt;/tt&gt; elements are typed as &lt;tt&gt;xsd:string&lt;/tt&gt; instead of &lt;tt&gt;xsd:ID&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Determine what to do with this value in the &lt;tt&gt;spring-beans-3.1.xsd&lt;/tt&gt;: preserve, deprecate (read: eliminate from 3.1, but still support in the parser for those who use &amp;lt;= 3.0 xsds), etc.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also update the relevant sections in the reference documentation as appropriate, including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;3.4.2.1 (the idref element)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;3.4.2.2&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

</description>
